            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Going to experiment with this separately, but if we get rid of the `--lazy-loading` option completely and always let the server fail on initial errors, we can match the semantics of `app.run()` and `flask run` at this point. `flask run` can be a call to `app.run()`, reducing a lot of duplication.\r\n\r\ncc @miguelgrinberg "
        },
